<%# app/views/trust_center/docs/anonymity-aggregation.html.erb %>

<div class="trust-doc">
  <div class="trust-doc-header">
    <div class="trust-doc-breadcrumb">
      <%= link_to "Trust Center", trust_home_url, class: "trust-doc-breadcrumb-link" %>
      <span class="trust-doc-breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
      <span class="trust-doc-breadcrumb-current">Aggregation & Anonymity</span>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-title-row">
      <%= image_tag "logo.png", class: "trust-doc-logo", alt: "Workplace.io" %>
      <div class="trust-doc-title">Aggregation & Anonymity</div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-subtitle">
      How Workplace.io structures reporting to emphasize aggregate insights, reduce individual-level exposure, and support customer governance.
      This page describes principles and controls without revealing proprietary analytics details.
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-updated">Last updated: <%= @trust_center_stamp %></div>
  </div>

  <div class="trust-doc-body">
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Core approach</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Workplace.io is designed to produce organization-level insights. Customers structure reporting using workspaces and groups. We encourage
        governance practices that reduce identification risk and discourage use for individual monitoring.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Workspace scoping:</strong> access is scoped to workspace membership.</li>
        <li><strong>Group-based views:</strong> customers can create groups to structure reporting and comparisons.</li>
        <li><strong>Short-lived message content:</strong> message content is processed briefly and removed; derived metadata is retained.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Anonymity considerations</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Anonymity risk increases as group size decreases. Customers should avoid configuring reporting in a way that isolates individuals.
        Where applicable, Workplace.io may hide or limit certain views for small groups to reduce identification risk.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Group size:</strong> small groups can increase the likelihood of identifying individuals.</li>
        <li><strong>Role governance:</strong> limit administrative access and sensitive views to trusted operators.</li>
        <li><strong>Interpretation:</strong> treat insights as indicators and use them alongside human context and judgment.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-callout trust-doc-callout--note">
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-title">Customer governance</div>
        <div class="trust-doc-callout-text">
          Customers are responsible for configuring groups and access policies in ways consistent with local law and internal HR/privacy policies.
          Workplace.io provides tools and guidance to support safer configurations.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Recommended deployment practices</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        For privacy-preserving deployments, we recommend the following practices.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li>Use group-level reporting rather than individual tracking.</li>
        <li>Limit administrative access to a small set of trusted operators.</li>
        <li>Define an internal policy for how insights may be used (e.g., improvement planning vs. discipline).</li>
        <li>Disconnect integrations that are no longer needed.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Acceptable Use (Culture Insights) →", trust_doc_url_for("acceptable-use"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Access Controls →", trust_doc_url_for("access-controls"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-footer">
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-title">Need guidance on safe configuration?</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-text">
        Contact us for recommended deployment patterns aligned with your organization’s privacy and governance requirements.
      </div>
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-actions">
        <%= link_to "Contact Trust & Security", trust_doc_url_for("contact"), class: "trust-doc-button" %>
        <%= link_to "Back to Trust Center", trust_home_url, class: "trust-doc-button trust-doc-button--secondary" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
